{
  "texts": [
    "Note, transportability analysis has been found to be possible even when harmonizing observational and random control trial (RCT) data 88.",
    "Moreover, data harmonization can also increase the possibility of using methods which rely on increased sample size and data variation.",
    "For instance, it can facilitate the exploration of interactive effects of variables within the data 89, 90 or make possible subgroup analyses to identify variation in within-sample effects 91, 92.",
    "Note, subgroup analysis divides a sample into different subsets based on an observable characteristic (e.g.",
    "gender, age) in order to investigate whether treatment effects differ among them."
  ]
}